Master Asset Checklist: Phaser 4 Rendering
Global Assets
UI/HUD Sprites (Phaser side):
Proximity/Threat Indicator (A minimalistic, sterile UI ring or line that tightens as enemies approach).
Thermal Load Tracker (For Arc 2/3 - simple geometric blocks filling up, not a standard "health bar").
Airflow Indicators (Subtle, semi-transparent directional arrows or drifting dust motes to show The Current).
Arc 1: The Configuration (Rowan Ibarra)
Theme: Micro-perfect, sterile, oppressive brightness. No dirt, no shadows, no humanity.
Tileset 1: NW-SMAC-01
Floors: Pristine white/blue ceramic tiles. High gloss.
Walls: Smooth, unblemished synthetic stone with harsh 90-degree corners.
Decorations: Sterile server racks, standardized orderly carts, perfectly aligned lighting strips.
Doors: Standard sliding bulkheads (Clean).
Interactables
Session Terminal: A sleek, upright console. Needs two states: Idle and Active (jacked in).
Mesh Uplink: A heavy, floor-mounted transmission node (The extraction point).
The Fragment Box: A bulky, heavy black cube (Item drop on the floor).
Characters (Animations: Idle, Walk, 4-Direction)
Rowan Ibarra: Dressed in a drab, standardized orderly uniform. Must look entirely unremarkable.
Rowan (Encumbered): A critical secondary animation set. Rowan visibly struggling to carry the heavy Fragment Box. Slower frame rate, hunched posture.
Commonwealth Enforcers: Faceless, heavily armored, moving with rigid, synchronized mathematical precision.
Arc 2: The Baffle (The Finder)
Theme: Corrosion, heavy shadows, mythic decay. The pristine geometry of Arc 1 is crushed and rusted.
Tileset 2: The Feral Surface
Floors: Rusted iron grating. Deep, dark gaps where the floor has fallen away.
Walls: Massive, curved acoustic baffles and stationary turbine blades. Covered in dark, caustic sludge.
Decorations: Bioluminescent mold colonies (used for faint light), piles of unidentifiable crushed machinery.
Doors: The "Judging Doors." Massive blast doors that are visibly stuck off-axis.
Interactables
Corrupted Terminals: Smashed screens with exposed, sparking wire.
Pneumatic Levers: Heavy, rusted mechanical switches to alter airflow. Needs Left and Right (or Open/Closed) states.
Characters & Hazards
The Finder: Bulky silhouette. Wrapped in thick, woven filter-mesh. A heavy physical "Reader" terminal strapped to their chest.
MITE-3 Swarm: This shouldn't look like a bug swarm. It should be an animated sprite of thermal distortion, static, and shimmering amber sparks.
Arc 3: The Heat Death (Sol Ibarra-Castro)
Theme: Claustrophobia, extreme temperature, structural collapse. The void is outside.
Tileset 3: The Citizen Lattice
Floors: Heavy industrial plating, visibly buckling or glowing dull red from heat stress.
Walls: Cramped service shafts wrapped in insulated piping.
The Void: Background tiles for outer space (visible through sheared-off sections of the station). Just deep black and the violent, expanding orange fire of the dying sun.
Doors: Emergency airlocks.
Interactables
The Archive Terminal: The final console. Needs to look ancient but heavily shielded.
The Payload Cannon: A massive railgun/launch tube structure occupying a large portion of the final room.
Characters & Hazards
Sol Ibarra-Castro: A utilitarian, heat-shielded maintenance suit. Stripped of all Commonwealth insignia.
Structural Shears: Floor tiles that visibly crack when stepped on, requiring a different sprite for Intact, Stressed, and Destroyed.
